{{italic title}}

'''''The Little Red Book of Acoustics''''' is a small book giving an overview of UK acoustic [[Regulation|regulations]]. The book also gives an introduction to [[acoustics]] and acoustic definitions.

This acoustics book is often used by professionals working in areas where some understanding in acoustics is required such as members of the [[Chartered Institute of Environmental Health]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cieh.org/ehn1/article.aspx?id=5468 |title=Sound Advice:The Little Red Book of Acoustics|accessdate=2007-11-19 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071031012558/http://www.cieh.org/ehn1/article.aspx?id=5468 |archivedate=2007-10-31 |df= }}</ref> and Town Planners.<ref>[https://archive.is/20070625081909/http://www.planningresource.co.uk/rtpi/674901/Handbook-helps-issue-acoustics-accessible/]</ref>

The book is also useful for students undertaking the [[Institute of Acoustics]] Diploma and similar courses. <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ioa.org.uk/diploma.asp |title=Institute of Acoustics: Diploma in Acoustics and Noise Control |accessdate=2007-07-31 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070702011443/http://www.ioa.org.uk/diploma.asp |archivedate=2007-07-02 |df= }}</ref>  ''The Little Red Book of Acoustics'' is one of the most popular books on the subject of acoustics for students and those new to acoustics in the UK.

Additionally the book provides a handy introduction to acoustics for [[Architect|architects]], covering for example, Approved Document E and is available on the [[Royal Institute of British Architects|RIBA]] bookshop website as well as the main UK bookshops.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ribabookshops.com/site/viewtitle.asp?sid=&pid=9227&HID=|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130201175328/http://www.ribabookshops.com/site/viewtitle.asp?sid=&pid=9227&HID=|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2013-02-01|title=Architecture Books, Contracts & Regulations {{!}} RIBA Bookshops|website=www.ribabookshops.com|access-date=2018-02-10}}</ref>

The book is written by Richard Watson and Owen Downey and published by Blue Tree Acoustics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bluetreeacoustics.com|title=Acoustic Consultancy, Noise Assessments and Air Tightness Testing in Sheffield, Leeds, Nottingham, Manchester and London - Blue Tree Acoustics|website=www.bluetreeacoustics.com|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080405173109/http://www.bluetreeacoustics.com/|archivedate=2008-04-05|df=}}</ref>  The second edition is released in September 2008 and is {{ISBN|9780956001207}}.

